luding `cartservice` and `paymentservice`.\n\n### Next Step\nUsing the anomalies listed, I will cross-reference the node-to-pod mapping to associate specific pod-level and node-level issues, highlighting primary root causes. \n\nAnalysis results in JSON format will follow.\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"NEUTRAL\",\n  \"detected_metric_keys\": [\n    \"node_filesystem_usage_rate\",\n    \"node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes\",\n    \"pod_cpu_usage\",\n    \"rrt_max\",\n    \"error_ratio\"\n  ],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"aiops-k8s-06\",\n      \"reason\": \"High filesystem usage rate (`node_filesystem_usage_rate`) spiked from 53.72% to 80.74%, potentially impacting performance across pods hosted on this node.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Normal median: 53.72%, fault median: 80.74%, change ratio: +40.19%\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"aiops-k8s-08\",\n      \"reason\": \"Memory exhaustion likely caused by a drop in available memory (`node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes`) on node `aiops-k8s-08`, affecting hosted pods.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Normal median: 11.66 GB, fault median: 9.66 GB, change ratio: -18.73%\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"redis-cart-0\",\n      \"reason\": \"Pod `redis-cart-0` experienced significant CPU usage spikes (`pod_cpu_usage`) during the fault period, possibly linked to node pressure.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Normal P99: 0.04 cores, fault P99: 0.11 cores, change ratio: +102.25%\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"cartservice-0\",\n      \"reason\": \"The service `cartservice` exhibited degraded performance metrics (`rrt_max` and `error_ratio`) suggesting service-level impact beyond resource exhaustion.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"rrt_max: Normal P99: 9762.5 ms, fault P99: 5157.32 ms, change ratio: -61.73%. Error ratio: Fault P99: 11.48, change ratio: +200%\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```"}
